  "text": "In particular, our sample of 488 bonds as of June 2000 include 245 bonds issued by borrowers which have bonds that are issued both under English law (i.e., with CACs) and under New York or German laws (i.e., without CACs) in our sample. 18 These bonds are issued by 29 different borrowers, including most of the largest emerging market sovereign borrowers over the last ten years, and are representative of the full range of the ratings spectrum. 19 If we can control for effects of the other characteristics of the bonds (such as maturity, currency, liquidity, etc) then by including a dummy for each issuer we can directly estimate the impact of governing law on spreads. This corresponds to a fixed effects identification strategy for selection bias [CITATION_1] .",
